&lt;p&gt;Xos is seeking a dynamic Senior Accountant, Payroll and General Accounting who brings strong expertise in managing payroll operations with accuracy and compliance. As a key member of the Finance and Accounting team, this role is responsible for overseeing end-to-end payroll processing while ensuring compliance with federal, state, and local regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to payroll operations, this role supports broader general accounting functions, including preparing payroll-related journal entries, assisting with audits, contributing to month-end close activities, and supporting financial reporting. The ideal candidate has deep payroll knowledge, strong analytical and problem-solving skills, and the ability to work both independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;**This is an on-site based role at our Los Angeles, CA HQ, offering a hybrid work model with more days in the office**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payroll and Restricted Stock Unit (RSU) Release, Processing &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process payroll using HRIS (Rippling), ensuring accurate calculation of wages, salaries, hours worked, paid leave, holiday pay, compensatory time, and overtime.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile payroll data, including insurance deductions, vacation time, 401(k) contributions, and other benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
